{
  "stem": "13817.4",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Either you-- you could march or you couldn't march.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "If you fell behind, there was a so-called medic in the back with his gun.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he would just push you into the-- into the ditch on the side of the road, would shoot you.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was-- my strength wasn't too bad at that time, because like I said before, I would take chances to get extra food.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "For instance, one time we-- when we went back to the camp before they entered through the camp, sometimes they would search us, the guards.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I was caught with a bag of sugar one time and I got a beating for it and I got 10-- 10 whips for it.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I still kept on doing it, because that was the only way to survive.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that was one thing what happened.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "What happened also in Janina is the only person I know who really escaped, did escaped.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the one who-- who escaped, I found out later on after he was gone he was a Polish army-- a Polish quite high officer.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he got in contact with the Polish Underground.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And one of the-- which one I don't know-- one of these coal miners got involved in it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he was the only one who I know who was able to escape.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And for that, we had to stand at attention when we weren't working for three full days in-- in the middle of winter and no food.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And the the guards were sent back to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We got new guards, which were a lot worse than the ones we had.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
